MIME media type name : Application

MIME subtype name : Vendor Tree - vnd.adobe.fxp

Required parameters : None.

Optional parameters : None.

Encoding considerations : binary
This media type may require encoding on transports not capable of handling binary.

Security considerations :
This media type is a zip package which may typically contain XML source
files, ActionScript files, and image assets for a Flex project. However,
the zip package may contain any files that a user decides to add to their
project, including executable files.

Contents of the package do not need privacy or integrity services.

The Adobe software security team reviewed this file format and found no
concerns. No other information is available at this time.

Interoperability considerations :
None.

Published specification :
No public specification.

Applications which use this media :
Authoring tools may use this file type for interchange of graphics; for example,
Adobe Flash Builder, Adobe Flash Catalyst and Adobe InDesign.

Additional information :

1. Magic number(s) : PK
2. File extension(s) : .fxp, fxpl
3. Macintosh file type code : None.
4. Object Identifiers: None.



Person to contact for further information :

1. Name : Steven Heintz
2. Email : heintz&adobe.com

Intended usage : Common
The file type is meant to enable the exchange of Adobe Flex projects between
capable applications.

(file created 2010-01-13)
